summary: SummaryHighlightsClean IngredientsCruelty FreeVeganSustainable PackagingGive BackDermalogica's Age Reversal Eye Complex targets and reverses the signs of skin aging, wrinkles and dark circles specifically formulated for the delicate eye area.
details: DetailsBenefitsDelivers age-fighting actives deep into the skinBest for those concerned with dark circles, fine lines and wrinkles around the delicate eye areaKey IngredientsAdvanced, Microencapsulated Retinol: helps smooth away the signs of skin aging around the eyesMicroencapsulation Technology: optimizes retinol potency and absorption to help reduce the appearance of fine linesMicroencapsulated Niacinamide and Ash Tree Bark Extract: maintain hydration and reduce visible dark circlesAge Reversal Firming Complex: works synergistically with antioxidant vitamin C, powerful peptides and botanical extracts to fortify and smooth skinFormulated WithoutParabensSulfatesPhthalatesSynthetic FragranceItem 2223879How To UseStart using alternate nights, for the first two weeks. As skin responds and increases tolerance, build up to using nightly. After cleansing, smooth and pat around the eye area working from the outer corner, inward.IngredientsWater/Aqua/Eau, Dimethicone, Methylheptyl Isostearate, Cetyl Alcohol, Diglycerin, Cyclopentasiloxane, Pentylene Glycol, Prunus Armeniaca (Apricot) Kernel Oil, PEG-100 Stearate, Glyceryl Stearate, Isohexadecane, Dimethicone Crosspolymer, Leuconostoc/Radish Root Ferment Filtrate, Retinol, Palmitoyl Oligopeptide, Palmitoyl Tetrapeptide-7, Arginine/Lysine Polypeptide, Sodium Ascorbyl Phosphate, Camellia Sinensis Leaf Extract, Caffeine, Aleurites Moluccana Seed Oil, Tocopheryl Acetate, Urea, Glucosamine HCl, Algae Extract, Yeast Extract, Tremella Fuciformis Polysaccharide, Fraxinus Excelsior Bark Extract, Niacinamide, Oryza Sativa (Rice) Bran Extract, Glycyrrhiza Glabra (Licorice) Root Extract, Hydrolyzed Soy Protein, Bisabolol, Cucumis Sativus (Cucumber) Fruit Extract, Saccharomyces Lysate Extract, Hesperidin Methyl Chalcone, Steareth-20 , Dipeptide-2, Avena Sativa (Oat) Kernel Extract, Medicago Sativa (Alfalfa) Seed Extract, Hydrolyzed Lupine Protein, Corallina Officinalis Extract, Dimethiconol, Glycerin, Butylene Glycol, Silanetriol Potassium Citrate, Aminomethyl Propanol , Acrylates/C10-30 Alkyl Acrylate Crosspolymer, Oleth-20, Carbomer, Polysorbate 20.Shipping & Coupon RestrictionsThis brand is excluded from most Ulta Beauty coupons.See brand eligibility details
how_to_use: Start using alternate nights, for the first two weeks. As skin responds and increases tolerance, build up to using nightly. After cleansing, smooth and pat around the eye area working from the outer corner, inward.

reviews.headline: I would buy this again and again
reviews.comments: Loyal to Dermologica products. This mist makes my skin feel and look good. I have been using it for a  few years and will continue to use it

reviews.headline: Will abosolutely buy this again
reviews.comments: This is indeed awesome.

reviews.headline: Favorite product!
reviews.comments: Works great!

reviews.headline: I have bought this spray many times.
reviews.comments: This is a lightweight toner that distributes well and smells great. While damp I add my serum and it melts into my face and neck area.

reviews.headline: Great summertime moisturizer
reviews.comments: This lightweight, non-fragranced moisturizer works best for warmer weather. It's a little bit on the watery side, but it's hydrating enough and absorbs quickly.

reviews.headline: Excellent product for sensitive skin
reviews.comments: I purchased this moisturizer for my daughter at the recommendation of our esthetician. Her skin is sensitive and she experiences seasonal eczema which requires a moisturizer which is appropriate to those needs.

reviews.headline: I would buy again.
reviews.comments: My go to eye cream

reviews.headline: Works well but it burns!
reviews.comments: This is the best eye cream I've used in years. I can see improvement already and I've only been using it for 3 weeks. The only thing I don't like is that it burns my eyes. I have to be extremely careful not to get it close to my eyes otherwise it seeps in burns. Then I have to rinse the whole eye and start over. Which is counterproductive seeing as though it's made for the eyes.

reviews.headline: Holy grail product!
reviews.comments: I'm cheap and don't like spending too much money on anything if I can avoid it. But I have the most ridiculous acne I've ever met. I'm in my early 30s and until I started using this I couldn't get it under control. I still have a few blemishes here and there but nothing like what I had before. I no longer wake up feeling super oily, and it dries my acne out overnight. The price is worth it!

reviews.headline: I would and have bought this product over the years
reviews.comments: This is a favorite of mine. It used to be much, much less expensive though.  Because of this, I do not purchase it as often as I used to.  I watch for deals and when one comes up, I buy it.

reviews.headline: Active Moist doesn't work
reviews.comments: my skin is dry/acneic so I decided to try this moisturizer out. It was stinging/burning a lot on my skin. It didn't seem to have any active ingredients to cause this type of discomfort. My sister and mom also tried it and they were not impressed at all.

reviews.headline: Product has changed
reviews.comments: I have used this product for years but they changed the product. It now has a musty not fresh scent. My last bottle arrived in a sealed box but had clearly leaked as the box was wet. Disappointed. This used to be a great product.

reviews.headline: Love! Love!
reviews.comments: I love this product. Wash your face, dry and spray!  Once my make up has set I always spray one more time to give it a look of being hydrated.

reviews.headline: Unpleasant fragrance
reviews.comments: I usually really like the smell of Dermalogica products, but this one--nope. Unpleasant fragrance; probably won't repurchase. Otherwise seems fine, but pricey.

reviews.headline: Best ever facial mist
reviews.comments: This is the very best antioxidant facial mist I've ever used, not only moisturizes but it also good as a makeup primer and setting spray.

reviews.headline: Good Moisture
reviews.comments: This has been my go to moisturizer for the past 2 years now. It works well. Easy to apply. The consistency is good, not too thick or too thin. I never feel greasy after. I will definitely continue to purchase.

reviews.headline: This is now in my regular arsenal.
reviews.comments: I love it.

reviews.headline: #1 Moisture
reviews.comments: I have very sensitive skin and this moisturizer is very hydrating and not thick. You don't have to use much. Itll last you a long time .

reviews.headline: Would recommend for my age
reviews.comments: First I think its important to disclose your age and skin type as your skin changes at different stages in life. I'm 39, and have dry skin. I picked this up along with several other dermalogica products and have been using them for 4 months. I wanted to use it for a while before reviewing. This is probably my favorite dermalogica product. It works well for my skin type. It's a light, fragrance free moisturizer. Doesn't irritate my skin. I use it daily. The downside is obviously the cost. I do get dry patches on my skin from time to time that I have to use a heavier moisturizer on, but daily use this is a great product.

reviews.headline: Not for me
reviews.comments: I have sensitive skin that is very temperamental when it doesn't like an ingredient. It's otherwise clear, and combination. I used this for several days and it started breaking me out immediately. With so many pimples cropping up, it's a no for me. May be the lavender? I'm not sure.

faceoff_positive.comments: This is the 1st product I have ever reviewed in my life, but it is so good I just had to write this one. At the age of 44 after trying almost every eye product on the market I had resigned myself to the fact that the dark circles around my eyes were something I would just have to live with, everything I have ever tried in the past made not even the slightest bit of difference. I also have really sensitive eyes and wear contact lenses and as such a lot of products make my eyes really red and sore. After reading some amazing reviews on the Internet I decided to give Dermalogica a go and got a few samples of the various products to try out. Two of the samples were this one (age reversal eye complex) and the Power firm. I tried the Power Firm sample first and although it was a lovely product to use and it did reduce some of the fine lines around my eyes I didn't notice any difference to my dark circles. Before the Power Firm sample ran out I decided to try the Eye Complex. This cream is so gentle, it didn't effect my eyes at all, even though I started using it twice every day and not every other day as recommended. I must admit that during the first couple of days of using it I didn't really notice a difference in my eyes at all, however on the 3rd day after waking up I looked in the mirror and actually said out loud 'Oh My God!' I could not believe it - my dark circles were really diminished and my eyes in general looked so much tighter and, well, just younger. Even though I had only had about 6 hours sleep and quite a few drinks the night before I looked fresh as a daisy, just as if I had had 10 hours sleep. Actually my eyes don't ever look this good no matter how much beauty sleep I get! It's been a week now and I am not joking, every day my eyes seem to be looking younger and younger and the dark circles are now virtually gone. The one little sample has only just run out as you only need a small amount for each eye, it really goes a long long way. I can't stop looking in the mirror, yes I know that sounds really vain but after all these years of trying rubbish products that promise the earth I just can't believe I have found something that actually does what it promises. Thank you Dermalogica!!!! I will definately be investing in the full size product of this miracle eye cream.
faceoff_positive.headline: My eyes look 10 years younger in 1 week!!!

faceoff_negative.comments: I've been using this product for over a month now, with a frequency of twice a day, as a preventative measure against wrinkles. You can see a difference immediately following application, as it smooths over the undereye area and evens out skin tone well. It's not magic, and I'm not noticing a major difference in my current fine lines, but the product feels nice and makes my make-up go on smoothly, so there is that.
faceoff_negative.headline: Not bad, not bad...
